>>61ff90fb-73e5-418b-afef-28763bf59dc0
I don't know about the flaws, the thing about the stashes is kinda true for most currencies but doesn't necessarily have to be that way.
The stuff about quantum is doubtful. Currently quantum computers are so powerful that you need to apply statistical methods to find the minute speedups provided by it to know whether they are actually any faster than a regular computer. It's not clear useful quantum computers will ever be developed.
And even if they are, it's possible to design QC-resistant public key cryptography methods.
